post_text:
Panther Fans-
Please make note of the following scheduling changes for this week:

1) The volleyball tournament at CRB scheduled this Saturday 9/5 has been canceled due to rising Covid-19 cases in Carroll County.
2) Volleyball will now play a JV/Varsity Thursday 9/3 scrimmage @ Glidden-Ralston. This is a closed scrimmage, with no parents or spectators allowed.
3) The football game this Friday 9/4 vs. Clarinda has been moved from Clarinda to Corning (SW Valley HS) due to Clarinda's field recently being reseeded and not yet ready for play.
- Please note for ALL spectators attending this game. MASKS/FACE COVERINGS ARE REQUIRED UPON ENTRY AND MUST BE WORN THE ENTIRE GAME. Panorama spectators will absolutely be abiding by these rules set by the host school. This will be policed/enforced at the game. Spectators not adhering to these rules will be asked to leave immediately and will face potential suspension to future Panorama events.

Reminder that our game Friday night (if WiFi allows) will be streamed at:
pantherlivestream.com

Because we are unable to host our Member Appreciation Picnic at the fair this year, the Board of Directors decided to participate in the fair by making a donation to the Guthrie County 4-H and FFA Youth Committee! The donation was made in the amount of $2,000 and will be used to help cover the committee’s expenses during the 2020 County Fair.

Pictured are some of our board members presenting their donation in the middle of August. (From left to right) Treasurer Curt Wilson, President Alex Durst, board member and youth committee member Steven Hameister, Vice President Jim Calvert, and Secretary Heath Blomquist.

It is mandatory that any HS student that has not completed a course schedule must communicate to do that this week. If regular school hours do not work for you this week - this Thursday, August 20th, the secondary is open noon to 8 p.m. for open house - you are invited to use this time.

**EVERY STUDENT WHO COMES TO OPEN HOUSE WILL RECEIVE FREE FACE SHIELD AND CLOTH FACE MASK IF WANTED.

Please be aware that participation in school activities requires being in a minimum of four courses during the season or corresponding school term.

Also, only students whose parent/legal guardian has communicated to school that it is ok for the student to leave school during open class periods may do so. Otherwise, a full six periods (8:20-3:15) of coursework will be expected.

Thanks and look forward to seeing everyone!!!

Principal Stanley

It would be great to see you from Noon to 8 p.m. on August 20th for our MS/HS Open House. Students are encouraged to bring school supplies and put in their locker. Hope to see you there!

MS/HS Open House Procedure:

Our teachers/office staff will be available from 12:00 pm to 8:00 pm.
Informational packets will be provided to each attending family.

When entering the building, please park in our east parking lot and enter the E5 doors (atrium). We ask that no one park in the drive in front of the main office.

One parent and/or the attending student will be allowed in the building. We are asking that siblings or other family members do not come into the building during the brief open house.

We encourage families to bring the students’ school supplies.

If you have forms and/or paperwork that need to be turned in to our office or nurse, they will be collected at this time.

When exiting the building, please use E6 (main office doors).

Social distancing guidelines will be in place during our Back to School Open House.

Face masks are encouraged.

We have been asked to put together a display for the Guthrie Co Fair this Labor day. We are looking for some history both physical and factual for our display. We are looking for some historical items such as Band or Choir items, Sweetheart items, etc that we can borrow for our display. We'd also like some historical facts that we might not have. Most of our information is in FFA scrapbooks from the merger but if anyone has some accurate data that might be of interest please let us know. You can email Mr. Hameister at steven.hameister@panorama.k12.ia.us and he will direct an FFA member your way. Thank you.

We will take information about the other county chapters as well that can go in our display.

post_text: The 2020 graduation ceremony for our seniors will be held July 19th at 1:00 p.m. in the Panorama Gymnasium. Seniors will need to meet in the old library at 11:00 a.m. This ceremony will also be live streamed to our public. Graduation invites will be sent out to our seniors and our junior ushers. Each family will be allotted five tickets to the ceremony. These will be sent with the invites. Seating will also be designated for families. Families will be ushered to their seats by one of our ushers. Families will also be dismissed by our ushers after the ceremony is completed. Seniors please bring your diplomas,cap, gown, tassel, stoll, and cords to the old library when we meet before the ceremony. More details will be sent out as we get closer to our graduation day.

Panorama travels to WCV this evening for the first baseball and softball games of the season. They will be attempting to Livestream these games (no guarantees of course!)
https://wcvwildcats.tv/?fbclid=IwAR06xr36xQDn6-he8FuVIVq_sAjAPb2bENGn0Y5MhL5t6nsQw0sXkwPbJMI

Softball Games start with Varsity at 5:30 & JV to follow.
Baseball Games start with JV at 5:00 & Varsity to follow.

Important reminders for those traveling to the game tonight:
-Follow social distancing guidelines
-No sunflower seeds/spitting allowed for players or fans
-No concessions will be available, bring your own items
-Games will be free will donation
-Stay away from all players, coaches, and umpires at all times
-No spectators near dugouts or designated team areas
-Be an awesome fan and keep comments encouraging and positive

WCVWILDCATS.TV
WCV Wildcats

Panther Pride Service Award

Purpose of the program: To impress upon the students the value that community service has in growing and building the communities in which they live. To help each student who participates to develop a sense of citizenship and leadership skills within their community. Community involvement is something that students can take with them as they become adults.

Volunteerism... is defined as the policy or practice of giving your time or talents for charitable, educational, or other worthwhile activities, within your community.

Congratulations to...
🎉Avery Norman for joining the 150 Club!
🎉Olivia & Gwen Steffen for joining the 100 Club!

post_text:
Panorama Families:

As Panorama CSD begins our “Return to Learn” plan for the fall of 2020 we need to have our stakeholders reflect and offer feedback on the distance learning that took place this spring. While we are extremely proud of the efforts of our staff and students this spring, it was our first experience with distance learning. A survey link has been sent to all parents and students 3rd through 12th grade. This survey will give our stakeholders an opportunity to share positives and offer recommendations to help us plan for a more effective fall 2020. At this point, we hope our educational experiences look traditional in the fall but the district needs to prepare for the potential of again utilizing distance learning.

We are asking all parents and 3rd-12th grade students to check their email and take this short survey.

Panorama Ffa
June 1 at 3:26 PM ·

Panorama Career and Technical Education department (Ag, Business, FCS) is looking for individuals who may be interested in being on their Advisory Committees. These are volunteers who agree to serve as an advisor to one of the programs. Members include representatives from business, labor, community agencies, etc. who would be willing to meet to help evaluate programs and basically make sure each program is meeting performance indicators. If you would be interested in learning more about what it takes to be on an advisory committee, please contact Mr. Hameister via email:

steven.hameister@panorama.k12.ia.us with the subject heading "Advisory Committee".

To: Current Juniors and Seniors

From: Mr. Stanley

Subject: Prom

Hello. Hope this message finds everyone safe and healthy. Following CDC guidelines, our prom will look different this year. We would like to still have a part of prom for this school year. This year we will only do the Grand March. This will take place up at the town square/gazebo.(More details will be given at a later time through email) Students will eat on their own and the dance portion of prom will be cancelled. We will make this as dressy as you want it to be. We will have a path for the march and a picture will be taken at the square. If interested, please fill out the Google Form with your names and the song you will want played during your march. As we find out the interest of our students, more details will be shared. Stay safe and healthy. This form is due by Monday, June 8th.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd6o8gHGKF9xDZn6gBIoRWQISAowYISn9o3Ii7NG49Et4QtHQ/viewform

post_text:
Panorama Families,

You are invited to a free virtual GEOSPATIAL TECHNOLOGY

VIRTUAL WORKSHOP,
TUESDAY, JUNE 16, 2020 8:30AM - 4:45PM

REGISTER AT:
https://arcg.is/1Xqay4

Areas of focus:
The basics of working with remotely sensed data using Geographic Information Systems (GIS) applications and opportunities for integrating Geospatial Technology into high school curriculum. How GIS and remotely sensed data can be used to characterize vegetation, soils and terrain, land, use/cover changes in the study of the environment, agriculture, ecology, & urban issues. ArcGIS Online and ArcGIS Pro, will be showcased for accessing, processing, and analyzing remotely sensed data such as those from unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs)-Drones, LiDAR, and Landsat Satellite imagery. Curriculum development mediated by available geospatial technologies within the framework of
current standards.

Thank you to CMSgt James M. Holwegner for looking out to any of our students and staff who may be interested in Ag/Drones/GIS technology and satellite technology.

Panorama Speech and Drama
May 19 at 9:09 PM ·

Our speech contest season is over this year. We held a virtual state contest along with ACGC this evening, and we are very proud of the students who chose to try this new way of doing speech. Learning to be flexible is a great life lesson!

There is a possibility of all-state nomination, and we will let you know as soon as we know!

Here are the results:

STRAIGHT 1’s
Ruby Hummel- Poetry
Shekynah Haworth- Acting
Alejandra Fuente Bonilla- Acting
Alejandra Fuente Bonilla- Solo Musical Theater
Lauren Soll- Prose

SPLIT 1’s (two 1's and a 2)
Lauren Soll- Poetry
Ruby Hummel- Public Address
Shekynah Haworth- Spontaneous Speaking
William Silva- Expository Address

SPLIT 2’s
Samantha Mortensen- Solo Musical Theater
Madison Livesay- Solo Musical Theater

Panorama Elementary is seeking an AmeriCorps member to serve as a reading tutor for the 2020-2021 school year. This person is not required to have a teaching license and will be provided literacy training and support. The tutor will be working 1:1 with students throughout the school day on foundational literacy skills.

If you have questions about the position please email liz.ratcliff@panorama.k12.ia.us.

If interested, please apply to AmeriCorps at the following link:
https://fs16.formsite.com/servetogrow/ciqxaxzpaa/form_login.html

post_text:
DATE: May 18, 2020

RE: Updated Graduation Details

TO: Class of 2020, Parents, and Community Members

The Panorama Community School District will hold graduation commencements on Sunday, July 19th. Our hope is still to have a traditional looking commencement ceremony outside at the athletic complex but we will also prepare for a virtual ceremony if CDC guidelines prohibit outside gatherings. More detailed information will be shared with seniors and their parents in the coming days.

Senior awards night will not be held on Wednesday, July 15th but our seniors will be honored through a video production that will include awards and scholarships received by our senior class

We have just over a week left of school, but if anyone else is looking for help feel free to send an email to carla.church@panorama.k12.ia.us

post_text:
Panorama Preschool Sign Up Information -

If you are looking to enroll your child in either our three year old or four year old preschool program, please visit our website at www.panoramaschools.org.

Once there, you can click on the "Parents" tab. You will then see the option to click "Preschool". The preschool handbook, brochure, and applications are at the bottom of the preschool page. The handbook and brochure will provide a brief overview of our program and class options.

Please feel free to fill out an application for your incoming preschooler and mail to Panorama Preschool P.O. Box 819 Panora, IA 50216.

We encourage families to send in their applications as soon as possible to ensure a spot for their child!

If you have any questions about our preschool program or enrolling your child, you are welcome to email Liz Ratcliff (Principal) at liz.ratcliff@panorama.k12.ia.us

post_text:
Panther Family-
As many of you have speculated, the West Central Activities Conference made an official vote today to cancel the upcoming JH softball and baseball season, which takes place during the month of June. This decision did not come lightly and there was much deliberation from the conference Athletic Directors. If you have any questions moving forward, please contact Panorama Activities Director, Erin Kirtley, @ erin.kirtley@panorama.k12.ia.us .

We are still hopeful to get a condensed summer season in for our high school students, which would start later in June. More information about these plans will be released according to guidelines from the state at a later date. Any 8th grade student going to be in 9th grade next year will have the opportunity to participate with the high school teams. Please notify Coach Bahrenfuss with baseball and Coach Nail with softball if interested.
brian.bahrenfuss@panorama.k12.ia.us
ryan.nail@panorama.k12.ia.us

Take care, Panthers!

Dear Panorama Parents and Families,

I wanted to update everyone that made an Art to Remember purchase this year from our Elementary students. First, I want to thank you very much for your support! And I wanted to let you know that due to the challenges everyone is facing right now our order delivery could be much later than expected. At the moment it looks like it might be late summer before it can be shipped. When I have a more precise date of delivery I'll make sure to let everyone know!

I sincerely thank you all! We have very talented kids at Panorama and I'm very PROUD to be their teacher! Stay safe!!
text:
Dear Panorama Parents and Families,

I wanted to update everyone that made an Art to Remember purchase this year from our Elementary students. First, I want to thank you very much for your support! And I wanted to let you know that due to the challenges everyone is facing right now our order delivery could be much later than expected. At the moment it looks like it might be late summer before it can be shipped. When I have a more precise date of delivery I'll make sure to let everyone know!

I sincerely thank you all! We have very talented kids at Panorama and I'm very PROUD to be their teacher! Stay safe!!

Panorama Schools is in need of used iPhone 6 cell phones (or newer). We are requesting your assistance in the hope that if you have upgraded and do not need your old phone and still have it - you would consider donating it to the school for student use as a hotspot, during this time of distance learning. If you have a device that you are willing to donate please contact us below to arrange drop off of the device:
Angie Clouser: angie.clouser@panorama.k12.ia.us
Vanessa Phillips: vanessa.phillips@panorama.k12.ia.us
We can also be reached at 641-755-2317

Thank you in advance for any assistance you can provide to our students during this time.

Following today’s Iowa PK-12 school closure update, all Iowa Girls High School Athletic Union (IGHSAU) and Iowa High School Athletic Association spring sports are officially canceled due to #COVID19.

📰 : https://ighsau.org/news/iowa-high-school-spring-sports-canceled/

We would like to thank our participants, coaches, administrators, officials, and fans for their passion, patience, and effort this spring. This is an especially unfortunate conclusion for the Class of 2020, and we’ll work to support them in the coming days. #iahsseniors

#IGHSAU #IowaGirl

post_text:
Our music fundraiser items will be delivered to the Panorama Elementary on Saturday April 18. The Middle/High School fundraiser (pastry puff) pickup will be from 9-11 a.m. and the 4th/5th grade fundraiser pick up will be from 1-3 p.m.

Please pull up to the elementary in the horseshoe drive. I will be out there to get your name. Stay in your cars. Someone will bring your items to me and I will hand them to you. I will have rubber gloves on...If this date or time does not work, either let me know or have someone else pick up your students items. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation!!

Please deliver to your customers at your convenience and safety.

Mr. Bauch
text:
Our music fundraiser items will be delivered to the Panorama Elementary on Saturday April 18. The Middle/High School fundraiser (pastry puff) pickup will be from 9-11 a.m. and the 4th/5th grade fundraiser pick up will be from 1-3 p.m.

Please pull up to the elementary in the horseshoe drive. I will be out there to get your name. Stay in your cars. Someone will bring your items to me and I will hand them to you. I will have rubber gloves on...If this date or time does not work, either let me know or have someone else pick up your students items. Thank you for your understanding and cooperation!!

Please deliver to your customers at your convenience and safety.

Mr. Bauch

post_text:
Starting tomorrow, Monday, March 23rd, free meals will be provided in "grab-and-go" style to those 18 and under on Mondays and Wednesdays during Panorama school closure due to COVID-19. Each of these dates students will be provided two breakfast meals and two lunch meals.

Details below:
Drop off at 11:30 a.m. - 11:45 a.m in Yale, Jamaica, Linden, Bagley & Panora (Drivers stay for 15 min. @ each location).
*Look for Panorama CSD vehicles sitting outside these locations

Bagley- Community Center
Yale- Memorial Park (Next to Community Building)
Linden- Post Office/Library on Main Street
Jamaica- Park next to Toe Joe’s
Panora- Library (North 1st Street)

Students do not need to be present to pick up meals and family member is allowed to pick up.
